venue.name: Memorial to the Murdered Jews of Europe (Denkmal für die ermordeten Juden Europas)

tip.text: very nice rooms w lovely local breakfast!
service is amazing! staff are gruff (it's part of the atmosphere) but very attentive and efficient. lovely casual atmosphere. and of course cheap+good beer made on the spot :D
nagasaki sara udon is HUGE. buta baranikku was amazing and of course umaki tama <3
tasty drag pom salad ($16 with a soup) and nut cheese ($18). currently their menu is very limited but will be expanded starting 1 march!
